search

Interface Frontier

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    EditableFrontier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BestFirstFrontier, BreadthFirstFrontier, DepthFirstFrontier

    public interface Frontier
    A Frontier encapsulates the collection of search Nodes (not States!) that are on the frontier of a frontier search (i.e. they have been discovered but not explored/processed to check whether they are a solution)
    Author:
    Simon Campbell

    • Method Summary

      Adds the provided node to the frontier.
      void clear()
      Clears the contents of a frontier so that it becomes empty.
      int getMaxFrontierSize()
      A method that returns the maximum number of nodes stored on the frontier since the frontier was created
      boolean isEmpty()
      Checks whether the frontier is empty
      Node remove()
      If the frontier is not empty, this method removes the next node from the frontier.
